description.narrative: ESARO worked closely with COs to strengthen evaluation quality and all UNICEF evaluations conducted in 2020 were rated “satisfactory” or higher by the GEROS criteria.Overall, the completion rates of the Evaluation Management Response (EMR) actions are timely, with good achievement of the 2021 target.ESARO supported the implementation of National Evaluation Capacity Development (NECD) activities in seven ESAR countries. Support was also provided for evidence-based programming in the COVID-19 response context, with Phase II of the real-time assessment of UNICEF’s country-level response finalized and an ESARO Compendium of Select 2020–2021 COVID-19 Response Lessons Learned completed. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/02/2022
